Package net.myorb.math.primenumbers

Implementations of algorithms supporting prime number use and factorization in particular.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FactorCollection
    the functionality required to represent a set of factors making up a value.
    Factorization.Underlying
    an underlying mechanism provides an expedited means of computing factorizations
    TableManager
    primitives required to drive generation of a table of prime factorizations
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Distribution
    an extended form of fraction used to represent a normalized form of Factorization
    DistributionScaling
    manage the sizes of fraction components
    FactorAdjustment
    evaluate a factorization and attempt to reduce "blob" size
    Factorization
    a factorization contains prime/exponent pairs plus the operators on those values
    Factorization.PrimeFactors
    a set of BigInteger prime values identifies the factors in a Factorization
    FactorizationFieldManager
    provide a type manager for integer values represented as prime number factorizations
    FactorizationImplementation
    build support structures for prime number factorization algorithms
    FactorizationImplementationUsingBitlength
    extending FactorizationImplementation to provide bitscale implementation of ListOfPrimes
    FactorizationManager
    an encapsulation of logic that performs prime factorization
    GenerationMonitorReport
    collect data about prime generation patterns
    ImplementationAccess
    static methods that expose access to implementation layer
    ReportGenerators
    generate reports from the prime factorizations tabulated

Package net.myorb.math.primenumbers Description

Implementations of algorithms supporting prime number use and factorization in particular.
